citeinfo.origin: Public Works and Transportation - GIS Division
citeinfo.title: CityLimit

descript.abstract: Digital, spatially georeferenced graphic representation of the city limits of the City of Dallas, Texas.
descript.purpose: To provide a current and accurate GIS database representing the geographic area of the City of Dallas.
descript.supplinf: Data sources include: City of Dallas ordinances, Zoning Maps, parcel data, dgn files, and DWU Lake Ray Hubbard Take Line Maps; North Central Texas Council of Governments 2000 aerial photos, 1990 and 2000 City Boundaries; electronic GIS data from the cities of Addison, Carrollton, Cedar Hill, Coppell, Farmers Branch, Garland, Grand Prairie, Irving, Mesquite, Plano, Richardson, Rowlett, University Park, and paper maps from the cities of Heath, Sunnyvale, and Highland Park.

idinfo.accconst: This information may contain licensed data and is furnished subject to license agreements with the City of Dallas.
idinfo.useconst: This data is to be used for graphical representation only. The accuracy is not to be taken/used as data produced by a Registered Professional Land Surveyor (RPLS) for the State of Texas.

dataqual.logic: To the knowledge of the creator, there are no inconsistencies to the data. The data seems to be complete. No specific test was run to test consistency. Polygon coverage is updated simultaneously with this line coverage.
